<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="879" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d879">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">King of Siam</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">White
                                        House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-10-15"><hi rend="italic">October 15,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>It has been a great pleasure to me to meet your son, not only on account
                            of my regard and esteem for Your Majesty, but also because of the
                            attractive character of the Crown Prince.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Theodore
                            Roosevelt.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>